      • setConfig

        public void setConfig(com.twitter.hbc.httpclient.auth.Authentication auth,
                      java.util.List<java.lang.String> terms,
                      boolean downloadMedia,
                      org.lightcouch.CouchDbProperties properties,
                      java.lang.String imgSize,
                      boolean mediaHttps,
                      com.twitter.hbc.core.endpoint.Location location)
               throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Sets the configuration for this TwitterStreaming instance, is required to be called in order to run a TwitterStreamer.
        Parameters:
        auth - OAuth authentication data
        terms - List of filter terms
        downloadMedia - true, if media downloader enabled, false to disable media downloads
        properties - CouchDB properties for the Crawcial Twitter Database
        imgSize - requested imgSize (thumb, small, medium, large)
        mediaHttps - true if https should be used for media downloads
        location - A geo location filter (optional)
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If your configuration is invalid

      • setLowMemory

        Sets the low memory status, is triggered by the media downloader, could be reset by the user.
